  "prompt": "How do l see who viewed my videos on Instagram?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Instagram does not provide a feature that allows users to see who viewed their videos, except for video profiles (the short looping videos that appear on your profile) and Instagram Stories. Here's what you can do:\n\n1. **Instagram Stories**: You can see who viewed your Instagram Stories by swiping up on the story while it's live. Instagram will show you a list of usernames of people who have viewed your story.\n\n2. **Video Profiles**: If you have a video as your profile picture, you can see the viewers by tapping on it from your profile page.\n\n3. **Regular Videos in Feed**: For videos posted in your feed, Instagram does not provide viewership data. You can only see the number of views, likes, and comments, but not the list of viewers.\n\nInstagram's policy on this helps protect user privacy. If you're looking for more detailed analytics, consider using Instagram's professional tools if you have a business or creator account. These tools can give you insights into your overall account performance but still won't list individual viewers of your videos.\n\nRemember, third-party apps that claim to offer this functionality might violate Instagram's terms of service and could compromise your account's security. It's best to avoid using such apps.",
